        -:  275:  * Output: \verbinclude DenseBase_LinSpaced.out
        -:  276:  *
        -:  277:  * For integer scalar types, an even spacing is possible if and only if the length of the range,
        -:  278:  * i.e., \c high-low is a scalar multiple of \c size-1, or if \c size is a scalar multiple of the
        -:  279:  * number of values \c high-low+1 (meaning each value can be repeated the same number of time).
        -:  280:  * If one of these two considions is not satisfied, then \c high is lowered to the largest value
        -:  281:  * satisfying one of this constraint.
